": "arabic", "text_bw": "bqr", "text_ar": "بقر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] and Lth says, it is called thus because it resorts ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaw^uwlu", "text_ar": "يَوُولُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") to the mountains: sometimes the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "j", "text_ar": "ج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the fem. is of the same three forms with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ayaAy^ilu", "text_ar": "اَيَايِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sayaAy^idu", "text_ar": "سَيَايِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "say~idN", "text_ar": "سَيِّدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Lth, T, Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=y^ilN", "text_ar": "ا=يِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["T", "K", "TA", "Msb", "S"]}, {"entry_id": "n1610", "headword_ar": "اـِيلُ", "root": "Ayl", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a name of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, S, M, K;) a Hebrew word; (Lth, S;) or Syriac: (S:) it is a dial. var. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_il~u", "text_ar": "اـِلُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]: or the latter may be an arabicized form of the former: (Az, TA:) Ibn-El-Kelbee says that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaboray^iylu", "text_ar": "جَبْرَيِيلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miykaAy^iylu", "text_ar": "مِيكَايِيلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like are similar to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eabodu A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaboda Alr~aHomaAni", "text_ar": "عَبْدَ الرَّحْمَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "t